---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Personal — Dakota Klatt"
  description="Beyond work: skiing, snowboarding, mountain biking, indie game dev, side projects. Green Bay, WI. Progress and mastery on and off the clock."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-section">
    <h1 id="main-content" class="font-display font-semibold text-display-xl text-[var(--color-text)] mb-4">
      Personal
    </h1>
    <div class="prose-custom text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-section">
      <p>
        Outside of work, I’m happiest doing something active or something I can build with my hands. In the winter that’s skiing and snowboarding; once the snow melts I’m mountain biking as often as I can. I like hobbies that reward consistency—show up, learn, get a little better—and it’s a great reset after a week of distributed systems, dashboards, and deployments.
      </p>
      <p>
        I’m also a tinkerer. I mess with drones and radio-controlled vehicles, and knock out home renovation/DIY projects. And when I’m in a software mood, I build for fun too: indie game development (systems/mechanics) and small tools or automations that make my workflow smoother. Same theme across all of it: iterate, simplify, and ship.
      </p>
      <p>
        I’m based in Green Bay, WI—Midwest weekends, four seasons, and any excuse to get outside.
      </p>
      <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mt-8 mb-3 text-base">Quick facts</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-text)] font-medium">Outside:</span> skiing, snowboarding, mountain biking</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-text)] font-medium">Tinkering:</span> drones & radio-controlled vehicles, DIY/home projects</li>
        <li><span class="text-[var(--color-text)] font-medium">Builder brain:</span> indie game dev + small tools/automation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <section class="border-t border-[var(--color-border)] pt-section" aria-labelledby="photos-heading">
      <h2 id="photos-heading" class="font-display font-semibold text-display-md text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6">
        Photos
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
        <figure class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-surface-elevated)]/30 overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="/images/personal-ski-group.png"
            alt="Group of people standing in snow with skis and snowboards on a winter slope."
            class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="p-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">Winter reset.</strong> Time on the mountain with friends.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-surface-elevated)]/30 overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="/images/personal-mtb-trail.png"
            alt="Person riding a mountain bike off a small feature on a dirt trail."
            class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="p-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">Trail season.</strong> Pushing skills and balance on the bike.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-surface-elevated)]/30 overflow-hidden">
          <img
            src="/images/personal-ski-crew.png"
            alt="Four people in helmets and winter gear standing near parked cars before a ski day."
            class="aspect-[4/3] w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption class="p-3 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
            <strong class="text-[var(--color-text)]">Trip crew.</strong> The people side of weekend adventures.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
